title: p9
text:
+++ title: “Notebook code” author: “Damien Martin” date: “2024-04-27” categories: [news, code, analysis] image: “image.jpg” description: “Hey Peter, what’s happening? We are going to need you to come in on Saturday, so if you can go ahead and just do that, that would be great.” +++

import plotnine as p9
import pandas as pd


df = pd.DataFrame({
    'x': [1,2,3],
    'y': [4,5,6]
})


(
    p9.ggplot(df, p9.aes(x='x', y='y'))
    + p9.geom_line()
)
